BRIEF DESCRIPTION:

Dine:
The dining philosopher program is an attempt to simulate the dining philosopher problem.
The program takes 2 arguments excluding the executable file. The first argument is the
total number of philosophers to sit at the table and the second argument is the number
of times each philosopher should eat to feel satisfied.

Made for and tested on Linux & Unix systems.

****************************************

COMPILATION:

make

****************************************

USAGE EXAMPLE:

Dine: ./dine 3 2
- 3 is the number of philosophers
- 2 is the number of times each philosopher should eat

****************************************

RUNTIME:

Example:

Dine:

make

./dine 3 2

Philosopher 1 is thinking
Philosopher 1 is eating
Philosopher 2 is thinking
Philosopher 2 is eating
Philosopher 3 is thinking
Philosopher 1 is thinking
Philosopher 3 is eating
Philosopher 2 is thinking
Philosopher 1 is eating
Philosopher 3 is thinking
Philosopher 2 is eating
Philosopher 1 is thinking
Philosopher 3 is eating
Philosopher 2 is thinking
Philosopher 3 is thinking

